    <briefdescription>
<para>Uniform source distribution in 1D. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This source property sets random x-coordinates according to a uniform source distribution in a given distance interval. If cosmological effects are included, this is done by drawing a light-travel distance from a flat distribution and converting to a comoving distance. In the absence of cosmological effects, the positions are drawn uniformly in the light-travel distance interval (as opposed to a comoving interval). The source positions are assigned to the x-coordinate (Vector3d(distance, 0, 0)) in this one-dimensional case. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
